How do we know we’re doing what’s best for our employees?





Previous Question
Next Question
Close Question




 
We’ll show you the way.
There are very specific rules governing your 401(k) plan, one of which is the obligation to make all decisions based on what is in the best interests of your employees. Though all plan sponsors have that obligation, unfortunately not all service providers working with retirement plans accept that same legal requirement.
As a fiduciary advisor, Buckingham serves as your true partner, helping you to satisfy this most important obligation.
Is your current advisor a fiduciary? Does your plan offer the right investment mix? Are the investments offered in your plan consistent with the guidelines in the Prudent Investor Rule? Are your employees getting the investment advice they need to make smarter decisions? Are they saving enough?
These are important questions to ask. If you’re not sure of the answers, give Buckingham a call. Talk to Buckingham today.


