What is risk?





Previous Question
Next Question
Close Question




 
Risk is inherent and essential.
When it comes to the financial markets, risk is commonly thought of in terms of the volatility or uncertainty that exists with any given investment. Ultimately, risk is an inherent and essential part of the markets as risk and expected returns are tightly related: the higher the perceived risk, the higher the expected returns.
At Buckingham, we work with our clients to understand and take into consideration a full spectrum of risks that may be present in their unique circumstances relative to investments, insurance, job security and diversification, tax liabilities and beyond. After we identify which risks exist, we craft the right strategies and plans to minimize any negative impact they may have, while appropriately capturing any opportunities they offer.


Related Insights
 
