Illinois Tool Works Inc. (NYSE:ITW) Stake Boosted by Buckingham Asset Management LLC

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 26th, 2017 // No Comments 

Buckingham Asset Management LLC increased its position in Illinois Tool Works Inc. (NYSE:ITW) by 1.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The institutional investor owned 1,793 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 29 shares during the period. Buckingham Asset Management LLC’s holdings in Illinois Tool Works were worth $238,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds also recently made changes to their positions in ITW. A.R.T. Advisors LLC acquired a new position in Illinois Tool Works during the fourth quarter valued at $2,939,000. Scotia Capital Inc. acquired a new position in Illinois Tool Works during the fourth quarter valued at $278,000. AMF Pensionsforsakring AB boosted its position in Illinois Tool Works by 59.6% in the fourth quarter. AMF Pensionsforsakring AB now owns 530,306 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $64,941,000 after buying an additional 198,079 shares in the last quarter. Tyers Asset Management LLC acquired a new position in Illinois Tool Works during the fourth quarter valued at $23,379,000. Finally, Parallel Advisors LLC acquired a new position in Illinois Tool Works during the fourth quarter valued at $264,000. 75.51% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Illinois Tool Works Inc. alerts:



Shares of Illinois Tool Works Inc. (NYSE ITW) traded down 0.357% on Wednesday, reaching $141.145. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 483,783 shares. The firm has a 50 day moving average of $145.59 and a 200 day moving average of $135.95. The company has a market cap of $48.76 billion, a PE ratio of 23.710 and a beta of 1.12. Illinois Tool Works Inc. has a 52-week low of $111.50 and a 52-week high of $150.29. 




Illinois Tool Works (NYSE:ITW) last issued its earnings results on Monday, July 24th. The industrial products company reported $1.66 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $1.63 by $0.03. The business had revenue of $3.60 billion during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $3.61 billion. Illinois Tool Works had a net margin of 15.50% and a return on equity of 46.57%. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 4.9% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the company earned $1.46 earnings per share. Analysts predict that Illinois Tool Works Inc. will post $6.38 earnings per share for the current year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, July 12th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 30th were issued a $0.65 dividend. The ex-dividend date was Wednesday, June 28th. This represents a $2.60 annualized dividend and a yield of 1.84%. Illinois Tool Works’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 42.07%. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY NOTICE: This article was first reported by BNB Daily and is the sole property of of BNB Daily. If you are reading this article on another domain, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of U.S. & international trademark and copyright legislation. The original version of this article can be accessed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/26/buckingham-asset-management-llc-acquires-29-shares-of-illinois-tool-works-inc-nyseitw-updated-updated.html. 
Several equities analysts have commented on ITW shares. Zacks Investment Research raised Illinois Tool Works from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $148.00 price target for the company in a report on Wednesday, March 29th. Deutsche Bank AG reaffirmed a “buy” rating and issued a $160.00 price target (up previously from $140.00) on shares of Illinois Tool Works in a report on Saturday, April 29th. Argus upped their price target on Illinois Tool Works from $145.00 to $160.00 and gave the company a “buy” rating in a report on Wednesday, April 26th. Jefferies Group LLC reaffirmed a “buy” rating and issued a $155.00 price target (up previously from $145.00) on shares of Illinois Tool Works in a report on Tuesday, April 11th. Finally, BMO Capital Markets reiterated a “buy” rating and issued a $145.00 price objective on shares of Illinois Tool Works in a research note on Thursday, April 20th. Six investment analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and eight have issued a buy rating to the company’s stock. The company has a consensus rating of “Buy” and an average price target of $152.58.
In other news, CFO Michael M. Larsen sold 52,447 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Friday, May 26th. The shares were sold at an average price of $140.62, for a total transaction of $7,375,097.14. Following the completion of the transaction, the chief financial officer now directly owns 67,383 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $9,475,397.46. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through the SEC website. Also, CEO Ernest Scott Santi sold 101,297 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Friday, May 12th. The shares were sold at an average price of $138.03, for a total transaction of $13,982,024.91. Following the transaction, the chief executive officer now directly owns 191,142 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $26,383,330.26. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders sold 201,961 shares of company stock valued at $28,311,650 over the last ninety days. Corporate insiders own 0.90% of the company’s stock. 
About Illinois Tool Works
Illinois Tool Works Inc is a manufacturer of industrial products and equipment. The Company operates through seven segments. The Automotive OEM segment produces components and fasteners for automotive-related applications. The Food Equipment segment offers commercial food equipment. The Test & Measurement and Electronics segment produces test and measurement, and electronic manufacturing and maintenance, repair and operations (MRO) solutions. 

 
